        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 25 at 1:43PM EDT until June 25 at 2:15PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Boydton, or 11
miles southwest of South Hill, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and powerlines.

Locations impacted include...
South Hill, Boydton, Beechwood, Bracey, Keats, John H Kerr Dam, Eppes
Fork, Baskerville, Palmer Springs, Lake Gaston, and John H Kerr
Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
